{"id":52465,"title":"Necrobiosis lipoidica.","abstract":"Necrobiosis lipoidica presents with a distinctive appearance making it an important clinical diagnosis.To describe a case of necrobiosis lipoidica in a patient with type 1 diabetes mellitus, and to discuss differential diagnoses and management.Necrobiosis lipoidica is most commonly found on the shins, presenting as a well-defined plaque. Management is challenging and options are discussed. Avoiding ulceration is a key concern.","date":"2014-03-06","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24600675","annotations":[{"name":"Diabetes mellitus","weight":0.840845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus"},{"name":"Medical diagnosis","weight":0.738937,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_diagnosis"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.738087,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Differential diagnosis","weight":0.729566,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_diagnosis"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.513077,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Diabetes mellitus type 1","weight":0.485358,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus_type_1"},{"name":"Ulcer (dermatology)","weight":0.376279,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulcer_(dermatology)"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.319691,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.0353015,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Necrobiosis lipoidica","weight":0.0329831,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Necrobiosis_lipoidica"},{"name":"Key (music)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Key_(music)"},{"name":"Differential (mechanical device)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedi